        {
            "review_id": "226938677",
            "steam_id": "76561199141576554",
            "playtime_minutes": 1596,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "It runs well on my M1 mac mini. The game is able to played at whatever level or intensity you want to experience and the multitude of Mods available will keep it fresh and flexible for many hours of play."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226882534",
            "steam_id": "76561198047361090",
            "playtime_minutes": 277,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Want to come home after a long day of work and work some more? This game is for you! Except its relaxing work, if there is such a thing. It is very satisfying working your way from the bottom and building your empire, but if you don't have the time for that, get the Government subsidies mod and let the money roll in so you can buy all the dream vehicles and attachments you'd ever want. I love forestry, so thats what I did. Living out my Lumberjack Dynasty fantasy here since they abandoned that game a while back."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226742078",
            "steam_id": "76561199051690606",
            "playtime_minutes": 38019,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Farming Simulator gave me something that to me, fell short short in most games. A real feeling of investment of time and energy developing fields, crops, watching markets for best opportunity to sell. Reinvesting in equipment for stronger stance for tomorrow. Watching a modest farm grow until you decide you are at the top. A lot of equipment I have used IRL was somehow exciting to use in a game. I honestly believe you will be hooked. The maps and equipment to use is endless, Yeah, You Deserve This!"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226559215",
            "steam_id": "76561197984044270",
            "playtime_minutes": 2518,
            "voted_up": false,
            "votes_up": 2,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "In the end, it becomes underwhelming. Farming isn't fleshed out enough in a game that is all about it. Like so many other games in the simulator genre, most of the work is put on licensed assets, while gameplay, QoL and depth takes the hit. Co-op is a major pull for this, but unless you want to be on the same farm and always play at the same time, the system is massively flawed. You're constantly missing deadlines and you'll need to prioritize playing the game before living your life."
        },
